verb.description: Accept or yield to a superior force or to the authority or will of another person.
examples: the original settlers were forced to submit to Bulgarian rule

verb.description: Subject to a particular process, treatment, or condition.
Present (a proposal, application, or other document) to a person or body for consideration or judgment.
examples: the panel's report was submitted to a parliamentary committee

origin: Late Middle English: from Latin submittere, from sub- under + mittere send, put. submit (sense 3)present for judgement dates from the mid 16th century.
